	<h2 id="public-heading" class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.1s">
		What Markets<br />Fail to Deliver
	</h2>
	<p class="section-intro reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.2s">
		South Africa's post-apartheid settlement preserved the economic
		architecture of apartheid while changing its political form. The
		Constitution guarantees housing, healthcare, food, water, and
		education as rights. The courts enforce these rights. And still,
		62% of children are poor, 32.9% are unemployed, and millions
		wait on housing lists that have grown longer every decade since
		1994. The record of other systems — flawed and constrained as each
		is — tells us this is not inevitable.
	</p>
